                            <comment id="465959" author="adilger" created="Fri, 1 Aug 2025 20:03:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Full debug log attached, collected with:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;# lctl set_param debug=all debug_mb=512
# mount --bind /myth /mnt/tmp
# lctl clear; lctl mark &quot;umount BEGIN&quot;; strace -o /tmp/umount.strace.txt -tt umount /mnt/tmp; \
  lctl mark &quot;umount END&quot;; lctl dk /tmp/umount.debug.txt
# mount --bind /myth /mnt/tmp
# lctl clear; lctl mark &quot;umount -f BEGIN&quot;; strace -o /tmp/umount-f.strace.txt -tt umount -f /mnt/tmp; \
  lctl mark &quot;umount -f END&quot;; lctl dk /tmp/umount-f.debug.txt
# umount /myth   ### because this mountpoint is now broken
# mount /myth
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;ll_umount_begin()&lt;/tt&gt; marking imports inactive happens almost immediately in the &lt;span class=&quot;nobr&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/attachment/59968/59968_umount-f.debug.txt.bz2&quot; title=&quot;umount-f.debug.txt.bz2 attached to LU-19222&quot;&gt;umount-f.debug.txt.bz2&lt;sup&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;rendericon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/images/icons/link_attachment_7.gif&quot; height=&quot;7&quot; width=&quot;7&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; file, but is not called at all in the &lt;span class=&quot;nobr&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/attachment/59970/59970_umount.debug.txt&quot; title=&quot;umount.debug.txt attached to LU-19222&quot;&gt;umount.debug.txt&lt;sup&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;rendericon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/images/icons/link_attachment_7.gif&quot; height=&quot;7&quot; width=&quot;7&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; log.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It looks like the trick now is to determine if a bind mount is being unmounted instead of the main/last mountpoint...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="465952" author="adilger" created="Fri, 1 Aug 2025 19:32:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It looks like the problem here is that the &quot;&lt;tt&gt;umount -f&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; process is calling &lt;tt&gt;ll_umount_begin()&lt;/tt&gt; &lt;b&gt;on every unmount&lt;/b&gt; which marks all of the imports inactive, instead of only when the superblock is being cleaned up and the connections dropped.  It looks like this &lt;em&gt;should&lt;/em&gt; be done when the superblock is being cleaned up, not when only a refcount to the existing mountpoint is dropped.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;/* umount -f client means force down, don&apos;t save state */&lt;/span&gt;
void ll_umount_begin(struct super_block *sb)
{
        :
        obd = class_exp2obd(sbi-&amp;gt;ll_md_exp);
        obd-&amp;gt;obd_force = 1;

        obd = class_exp2obd(sbi-&amp;gt;ll_dt_exp);
        obd-&amp;gt;obd_force = 1;

        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (ioc_data) {
                obd_iocontrol(OBD_IOC_SET_ACTIVE, sbi-&amp;gt;ll_md_exp,
                              sizeof(*ioc_data), ioc_data, NULL);
                obd_iocontrol(OBD_IOC_SET_ACTIVE, sbi-&amp;gt;ll_dt_exp,
                              sizeof(*ioc_data), ioc_data, NULL);
        }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
